\details{
Provides shared infrastructure for all Hyperliquid R6 classes: wallet
credentials, network selection, sync/async execution mode, the request
funnel (\code{\link[=hyperliquid_build_request]{hyperliquid_build_request()}}), and lazy exchange-metadata caching.
\subsection{Sync vs Async}{

The \code{async} parameter controls execution mode for all API methods:
\itemize{
\item \code{async = FALSE} (default): methods return results directly.
\item \code{async = TRUE}: methods return \link[promises:promise]{promises::promise} objects that resolve to
the same types.
}

Async mode requires the \code{promises} package (a \code{Suggests}). Consume promises
with \code{\link[coro:async]{coro::async()}} and \code{await()} or \code{\link[promises:then]{promises::then()}}; to drive the event
loop in a script use the (optional) \code{later} package, e.g.
\code{while (!later::loop_empty()) later::run_now()}.
}

\subsection{Hosts}{

The entire REST API lives behind one host with two POST paths: \verb{/info}
(public reads, unauthenticated) and \verb{/exchange} (writes, authenticated by a
wallet signature in the body). Only the network differs between mainnet and
testnet, and it is chosen by the explicit \code{testnet} flag, never by URL
sniffing: the network changes the signature itself (phantom-agent source and
\code{hyperliquidChain} tag). See \code{\link[=get_base_url]{get_base_url()}}.
}

\subsection{Design}{

This class is not meant to be instantiated directly. Subclasses (e.g.
\code{HyperliquidMarketData}, \code{HyperliquidTrading}) inherit from it and define
public methods that delegate to \code{private$.info()} (reads) or
\code{private$.exchange()} (signed writes). Each subclass method passes a
\code{.parser} closure and is otherwise sync/async-unaware.
}
}
\section{Fields}{

All fields are private:
\itemize{
\item \code{.keys}: List; wallet credentials from \code{\link[=get_api_keys]{get_api_keys()}}.
\item \code{.signer}: \link[ethsign:EthSigner]{ethsign::EthSigner} or \code{NULL}; the wallet signer built from the
key (used to sign /exchange actions), or \code{NULL} when no key is set.
\item \code{.base_url}: Character; REST base URL for the selected network.
\item \code{.is_async}: Logical; whether the instance is in async mode.
\item \code{.perform}: Function; \link[httr2:req_perform]{httr2::req_perform} or \link[httr2:req_perform_promise]{httr2::req_perform_promise}.
\item \code{.testnet}: Logical; whether the instance targets testnet.
\item \code{.vault_address}: Character or \code{NULL}; vault/sub-account to act for.
\item \code{.account_address}: Character or \code{NULL}; master account for an agent wallet.
\item \code{.meta_cache}: List or \code{NULL}; cached asset-lookup tables (lazy).
}
}

